body:
This change updates the VM service files to include the new methods that find resolved URIs and package URIs for files, so that we can use the VM for breakpoint mapping instead of the mapping method in `FlutterPositionMapper` (which does a combination of analyzer and other things). 

Only changes in the first file (`VmServiceWrapper`) are significant; the rest are generated file changes.

~I left some print statements in here for now as I haven't found a way to fix my Java breakpoints.~

comment_data.body: remove System.out.print here and elsewhere perhaps replacing it with proper logging if the prints could be relevant for future debugging.
need to make sure you aren't disposed by the time this callback is triggered.

I think you can make this more robust by using the bazel package root that should be
someDirectory/google3

that way something wacky like
someDirectory/google3/someDir2/google3
won't false positive.
nit: just make this "google3:///" as the fact that this google3 uri scheme happens to make the google3 root directory is somewhat arbitrary.
Check that project is not disposed?
